Standard and Poor's Corp said it mayupgrade Wainoco Oil Corp's 25 mln dlrs of C-rated subordinateddebentures due 1998.    S and P cited the company's proposed offering of two mlnunits of common stock and warrants, which would raise 25 mln to30 mln dlrs that would be used to retire bank debt.    The offering would also result in a significantstrengthening of the company's capital structure, S and Ppointed out. However, the agency said it would also considerdepressed industry conditions and Wainoco's ability to operatein that environment. Its implied senior debt rating is CCC. Reuter&#3;